      • setMetadata

        public void setMetadata(T subject,
                        String metadataKey,
                        MetadataValue newMetadataValue)
        Adds a metadata value to an object. Each metadata value is owned by a specific Plugin. If a plugin has already added a metadata value to an object, that value will be replaced with the value of newMetadataValue. Multiple plugins can set independent values for the same metadataKey without conflict.

        Implementation note: I considered using a ReadWriteLock for controlling access to metadataMap, but decided that the added overhead wasn't worth the finer grained access control.

        Bukkit is almost entirely single threaded so locking overhead shouldn't pose a problem.

        パラメータ:
        subject - The object receiving the metadata.
        metadataKey - A unique key to identify this metadata.
        newMetadataValue - The metadata value to apply.
        例外:
        IllegalArgumentException - If value is null, or the owning plugin is null
        関連項目:
        MetadataStore.setMetadata(Object, String, MetadataValue)

      • getMetadata

        public List<MetadataValue> getMetadata(T subject,
                                       String metadataKey)
        Returns all metadata values attached to an object. If multiple have attached metadata, each will value will be included.
        パラメータ:
        subject - the object being interrogated.
        metadataKey - the unique metadata key being sought.
        戻り値:
        A list of values, one for each plugin that has set the requested value.
        関連項目:
        MetadataStore.getMetadata(Object, String)

      • hasMetadata

        public boolean hasMetadata(T subject,
                           String metadataKey)
        Tests to see if a metadata attribute has been set on an object.
        パラメータ:
        subject - the object upon which the has-metadata test is performed.
        metadataKey - the unique metadata key being queried.
        戻り値:
        the existence of the metadataKey within subject.

      • removeMetadata

        public void removeMetadata(T subject,
                           String metadataKey,
                           Plugin owningPlugin)
        Removes a metadata item owned by a plugin from a subject.
        パラメータ:
        subject - the object to remove the metadata from.
        metadataKey - the unique metadata key identifying the metadata to remove.
        owningPlugin - the plugin attempting to remove a metadata item.
        例外:
        IllegalArgumentException - If plugin is null
        関連項目:
        MetadataStore.removeMetadata(Object, String, org.bukkit.plugin.Plugin)

      • invalidateAll

        public void invalidateAll(Plugin owningPlugin)
        Invalidates all metadata in the metadata store that originates from the given plugin. Doing this will force each invalidated metadata item to be recalculated the next time it is accessed.
        パラメータ:
        owningPlugin - the plugin requesting the invalidation.
        例外:
        IllegalArgumentException - If plugin is null
        関連項目:
        MetadataStore.invalidateAll(org.bukkit.plugin.Plugin)

      • disambiguate

        protected abstract String disambiguate(T subject,
                                       String metadataKey)
        Creates a unique name for the object receiving metadata by combining unique data from the subject with a metadataKey.

        The name created must be globally unique for the given object and any two equivalent objects must generate the same unique name. For example, two Player objects must generate the same string if they represent the same player, even if the objects would fail a reference equality test.

        パラメータ:
        subject - The object for which this key is being generated.
        metadataKey - The name identifying the metadata value.
        戻り値:
        a unique metadata key for the given subject.
